  entryId: rabbit_white
  commonName: White Rabbit
  scientificName: Oryctolagus cuniculus
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 9c1cc2802ceb63c499f4d7adef7d5851, type: 3}
  category: Mammal
  habitat: Grassland and woodland edges
  height: 0.20 m
  weight: 1.2 - 2.0 kg
  diet: Herbivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A nimble herbivore that stays alert, keeps close to cover, and reacts quickly to sound.
  behaviorNotes: Rabbits prefer quick changes of direction and short bursts of movement when startled.
  observationTips: Watch the ground level near bushes, paths, and terrain edges. Slow movement helps avoid spooking them.
  funFact: A rabbit can twist its ears independently to listen in multiple directions.
  facts:
  - The project already includes a rabbit demo prefab that can be turned into a targetable creature.
  - Rabbits are a natural early-game discovery because their silhouettes are easy to read.
  - They often freeze before running, which makes them memorable in VR.
